From 8bbaaf9564b9b4b7b43502ae5cfa0b4699d4fc55 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jeevan Kukkalli <jeevank@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 9 Sep 2025 13:25:18 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:DP:wifi:ath12k: Reset monitor descriptor before
 replenish

Currently if any error occurs during replenish we return the
monitor descriptors back to free list. Before we return we free any
allocated buffers associated with descriptor. If monitor descriptors
were not reset before replenish they may contain stale buffer address
and freeing them could lead to memory corruption. To avaoid this
always reset monitor descriptors before replenish.

Patch-dependency:
0495-04-Upstream-DP-wifi-ath12k-Support-Ethernet-packet-capt.patch

Signed-off-by: Jeevan Kukkalli <jeevank@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_mon.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_mon.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_mon.c
index cb043c0..0afeb3e 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_mon.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_mon.c
@@ -759,6 +759,7 @@ size_t ath12k_dp_mon_list_cut_nodes(struct list_head *list, struct list_head *he
 			break;
 
 		mon_desc = list_entry(cur, struct ath12k_dp_mon_desc, list);
+		ath12k_dp_mon_desc_reset(mon_desc);
 		mon_desc->in_use = true;
 
 		count--;
-- 
2.34.1

